100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 13, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing the ongoing economic challenges post-World War I and the importance of international cooperation. In Japan, the government announced new measures to address the rising tide of labor unrest, reflecting growing discontent among workers. Meanwhile, in the United States, the Scopes Trial continued to dominate headlines, as the debate over evolution in schools sparked national conversation about science and religion.
